# Talking Bin
## A working title

## Dependancies

* Ruby 1.9.3+ or 2+
* Pi_Piper Gem
* RealRand Gem
* MPlayer2
* Alsa Support

## Workflow

1. Parse the configured list of sayings into an array of strings
2. Get a list of truly random numbers from random.org
3. Receive external stimulus (GPIO, HTTP request etc.)
4. Select a random string from the array
5. Check if the saying wav is already cached
  1. Retrieve it and cache if not
6. Playback the saying wav with an external player
7. Wait for next stimulus
